Golden Path v0 Example Set
Example A: Hard Skill
Subject: MathSource mix: Common Core + Oxford + IBCanonical skill: Solve and explain one-step linear equationsWhy good for v0: clean, observable, portable, low ambiguity
Flow
* Source standard/content: solve simple linear equations, show working, interpret variables
* Derived skill: learner can solve and explain one-step linear equations in context
* Milestones:
    * isolate the variable correctly
    * perform inverse operation correctly
    * explain why the operation preserves equality
    * solve a one-step equation in a word problem
* Generated quest: “Crack the Code” equation mission
* Evidence submission: worked solution + short oral or written explanation
* Mastery decision: demonstrated / not_yet
* Portability record: verified mastery of one-step linear equations
Example B: Soft Skill
Subject: Human development / transferable skillSource mix: IB + Oxford + school SEL/objective language + TFSC framingCanonical skill: Adapt response when conditions changeWhy good for v0: proves many-to-one mapping and multiple valid evidence modes
Flow
* Source standard/content: reflect, adjust, respond to feedback, persist through challenge
* Derived skill: learner can adapt strategy when the original approach is not working
* Milestones:
    * identify that conditions changed
    * name at least one alternative strategy
    * try a new strategy appropriately
    * reflect on what changed and why
* Generated quest: “Mission Shift” team challenge with changed constraints midway
* Evidence submission: facilitator observation + peer feedback + learner reflection
* Mastery decision: demonstrated / not_yet
* Portability record: verified adaptability in changing conditions

v0 Design Rules
1. Preserve source
    * original text stays intact in Repository
2. Translate, do not erase
    * Skill layer normalizes without deleting source differences
3. Allow many-to-one mappings
    * multiple repository items can point to one skill
4. Allow multiple valid evidence modes
    * milestone proof is flexible, threshold is not
5. Reward demonstrated mastery, not one mandated path
    * equivalent paths are modeled in edges and evidence modes
6. Keep v0 binary
    * mastery decision is only demonstrated or not_yet
7. Keep Edventurefy secondary
    * foundation first, experience layer plugs in later

